cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of signal recovery from corrupted measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of regularization techniques and matrix deviation inequalities also suggests a connection to optimization (cs.OH) and linear algebra (cs.LA). However, since the focus is on sub-Gaussian measurements and structured signals, we can rule out some sub-categories such as cs.CV (computer vision) and cs.CR (cryptography).
